oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Parade on Elk Avenue
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a parade procession on Elk Avenue. Royal Crowne Cola, Southern Loans, Citizens Bank, and an insurance company are among the businesses seen. A marching band is walking through the street, and spectators and cars are on either side. Note the police car at the front of the procession.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Parades & processions; Stores & shops; Marching bands; Police cars
